# 凸优化极简入门

这篇博客记录了我学习凸优化的历程，所有的知识来源于```Berkeley```大学的```EE 227C (Spring 2018)
Convex Optimization and Approximation```课程。该课程非常易懂，学习凸优化同时，学习了很多很多的知识。
课程链接[ee227c](https://ee227c.github.io)。

### 凸集

什么是凸集？凸集的定义是一个集合 <a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$K\subseteq&space;R^n$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$K\subseteq&space;R^n$" title="$K\subseteq R^n$" /></a>,如果满足在<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$K$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$K$" title="$K$" /></a>中的任意两个点之间的连线所有的点仍在集合<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$K$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$K$" title="$K$" /></a>中，那么这就叫做凸集。一般的，对于<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$x,y&space;\in&space;K$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$x,y&space;\in&space;K$" title="$x,y \in K$" /></a> 以及 <a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$\gamma&space;\in&space;[0,1]$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$\gamma&space;\in&space;[0,1]$" title="$\gamma \in [0,1]$" /></a>,则有<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$\gamma&space;x&space;&plus;&space;(1-\gamma)y&space;\in&space;K$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$\gamma&space;x&space;&plus;&space;(1-\gamma)y&space;\in&space;K$" title="$\gamma x + (1-\gamma)y \in K$" /></a>。

### 凸函数

凸函数的定义对于一个函数 <a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$f:\Omega&space;\rightarrow&space;R$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$f:\Omega&space;\rightarrow&space;R$" title="$f:\Omega \rightarrow R$" /></a>,如果所有的<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$x,y&space;\in&space;\Omega$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$x,y&space;\in&space;\Omega$" title="$x,y \in \Omega$" /></a>并且 <a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$\gamma&space;\in&space;[0,1]$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$\gamma&space;\in&space;[0,1]$" title="$\gamma \in [0,1]$" /></a>,则有<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$f(\gamma&space;x&space;&plus;&space;(1-\gamma)y)&space;\leq&space;\gamma&space;f(x)&plus;(1-\gamma)f(y)$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$f(\gamma&space;x&space;&plus;&space;(1-\gamma)y)&space;\leq&space;\gamma&space;f(x)&plus;(1-\gamma)f(y)$" title="$f(\gamma x + (1-\gamma)y) \leq \gamma f(x)+(1-\gamma)f(y)$" /></a>。

直观上来看，该函数是类似一个碗状。至于为什么凸优化如此重要，就是因为这个世界，**我们需要解决的问题无非就是最大值最小值的问题**，而很多问题并不容易求解，于是我们需要将其转换为凸函数，再进行求解优化。至于机器学习中更加重要了，神经网络作为一个黑盒子，如何优化该黑盒子，成为重点，因为神经网络作为一个函数，但是具体函数具体怎么实现，我们不知道，于是通过其他方式来求解。

### 泰勒展开

对于任意的连续的，可微的函数来说，都有其对应的泰勒展开

<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$$&space;f(x)&space;=&space;f(x_0)&space;&plus;&space;f^{'}(x_0)(x-x_0)&plus;\frac{f^{''}(x_0)}{2!}(x-x_0)^2&plus;...&plus;&space;\frac{f^n(x0)}{n!}(x-x_0)^n&space;$$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$$&space;f(x)&space;=&space;f(x_0)&space;&plus;&space;f^{'}(x_0)(x-x_0)&plus;\frac{f^{''}(x_0)}{2!}(x-x_0)^2&plus;...&plus;&space;\frac{f^n(x0)}{n!}(x-x_0)^n&space;$$" title="$$ f(x) = f(x_0) + f^{'}(x_0)(x-x_0)+\frac{f^{''}(x_0)}{2!}(x-x_0)^2+...+ \frac{f^n(x0)}{n!}(x-x_0)^n $$" /></a>

当<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$x=0$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$x=0$" title="$x=0$" /></a>时，就变成了麦克劳林展开，一般的，可以在任意处展开。

### 凸优化的一些方法

其中，最主要的方法是**梯度下降**。

```python
def gradient_descent(init, steps, grad, proj=lambda x: x):
    """Projected gradient descent.
    
    Inputs:
        initial: starting point
        steps: list of scalar step sizes
        grad: function mapping points to gradients
        proj (optional): function mapping points to points
        
    Returns:
        List of all points computed by projected gradient descent.
    """
    xs = [init]
    for step in steps:
        xs.append(proj(xs[-1] - step * grad(xs[-1])))
    return xs
```

但是，有时候梯度下降慢，有什么办法求解呢？

**矩阵投影**，将一个范围内的点投影在**凸集**上,那么就很快的实现优化这一操作。

<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$$&space;P_A(x)&space;=&space;a&space;&plus;&space;P_S(x-a)&space;$$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$$&space;P_A(x)&space;=&space;a&space;&plus;&space;P_S(x-a)&space;$$" title="$$ P_A(x) = a + P_S(x-a) $$" /></a>

```python
def proj(x):
    """Projection of x onto an affine subspace"""
    return b + U.dot(U.T).dot(x-b)
```

那么，该优化为

```python
x_opt = proj(0)
```

### Black-box optimization

我们讨论一下```derivative-free optimization```,就是一种没有导数的优化方法。很难想象，如果没有求偏导来进行优化，那么该怎么优化？


目标：

<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$$&space;\min&space;\limits_{x}&space;f(x)&space;$$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$$&space;\min&space;\limits_{x}&space;f(x)&space;$$" title="$$ \min \limits_{x} f(x) $$" /></a>

#### Basic random search

1. Pick an initial point  x0
2. Iterate from  t=1:
    * Pick  <a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$d_t$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$d_t$" title="$d_t$" /></a> be a random direction in  <a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$R^n$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$R^n$" title="$R^n$" /></a>.
    * set <a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$&space;\eta^*&space;=&space;argmin_{\eta}f(x_{t-1}&plus;\eta&space;d_t)$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$&space;\eta^*&space;=&space;argmin_{\eta}f(x_{t-1}&plus;\eta&space;d_t)$" title="$ \eta^* = argmin_{\eta}f(x_{t-1}+\eta d_t)$" /></a>
    * put <a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$&space;x_t&space;=&space;x_{t-1}&plus;\eta^*&space;d_t$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$&space;x_t&space;=&space;x_{t-1}&plus;\eta^*&space;d_t$" title="$ x_t = x_{t-1}+\eta^* d_t$" /></a>

### 实现

那么如何来实现这样的算法呢？一个直观的算法为黄金分割算法[Golden-section_search](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden-section_search)

```python
def gss(f, a, b, tol=1e-5):
    """Golden section search
    
    Find the minimum of f on [a,b]
    f: a strictly unimodal function on [a,b]
    """
    gr = (np.sqrt(5) + 1) / 2
    c = b - (b - a) / gr
    d = a + (b - a) / gr 
    while abs(c - d) > tol:
        if f(c) < f(d):
            b = d
        else:
            a = c
        # we recompute both c and d here to avoid loss of precision which may lead to incorrect results or infinite loop
        c = b - (b - a) / gr
        d = a + (b - a) / gr
    return (b + a) / 2
```

那么，随机搜索如下

```python
def random_search(oracle, init, num_steps, line_search=gss):
    """Implements random search.
    
    oracle: Function.
    init: Point in domain of oracle.
    num_steps: Number of iterations.
    line_search: Line search method (defaults to golden section.)
    
    Returns: List of iterates."""
    iterates = [init]
    for _ in range(num_steps):
        d = np.random.normal(0, 100, init.shape)
        d /= np.linalg.norm(d)
        x = iterates[-1]
        eta = line_search(lambda step: oracle(x + step * d), -1, 1)
        iterates.append(x + eta * d)
    return iterates 
```

### example

```python
A = np.random.normal(0, 1, (100, 100))
b = np.random.normal(0, 1, (100,))
def least_squares(x):
    return 0.5*np.linalg.norm(A.dot(x)-b)**2

xs = random_search(least_squares, b, 1000, gss)
error_plot([least_squares(x) for x in xs])
```

### 强化学习45min入门

我们来考虑一个有意思的问题**flappy bird**。

> 假设我们有个小鸟，向前的速度是一定的为<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$v$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$v$" title="$v$" /></a>,小鸟垂直的位置<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$h$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$h$" title="$h$" /></a>与重力以及空气的阻力有关系，那么向下的加速度为<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$F=mg-kv$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$F=mg-kv$" title="$F=mg-kv$" /></a>,同时根据牛顿定律<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$F=ma$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$F=ma$" title="$F=ma$" /></a>,那么<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;\frac{dv}{dt}=g-(k/m)v" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;\frac{dv}{dt}=g-(k/m)v" title="\frac{dv}{dt}=g-(k/m)v" /></a>。

```python
def flappy_bird(state, action):
    """Flappy bird dynamical system.
    
    state: pair of downward velocity and height
    action: upward acceleration
    
    Returns new state."""
    v, h = state
    g = 1. # acceleration due to gravity
    k = 0.01 # drag coefficient
    m = 1 # mass
    return (v + g - (k/m)*v - action, h - v)

def unroll(system, inits, policy, num_steps):
    """Unroll a dynamical system."""
    states = [inits[0]]
    actions = [inits[1]]
    for _ in range(num_steps):
        action = policy(states, actions)
        actions.append(action)
        states.append(system(states[-1], action))
    return states, actions
```

假设现在有一个策略，每隔5s，就向上给一个**7**的加速度。

```python
def example_policy(states, actions):
    """Accelerate upwards every 5 steps."""
    v, h = states[-1]
    if divmod(len(states), 5)[1] == 0:
        return 7
    else:
        return 0.
```

那么

```python
flappy_inits = [(0, 10.), 0]
states, actions = unroll(flappy_bird, flappy_inits, example_policy, 10)
heights = [h for (v, h) in states]

plt.xkcd(); fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,10))
im = plt.imread('flappy.png')
fig.gca().imshow(im, aspect='auto', extent=(0, 1, 9.5, 10.5))
fig.figimage(im, 0, fig.bbox.ymax)
plt.ylabel('height'); plt.xlabel('time');
plt.plot(range(len(heights)), heights);
```

结果为

### 强化学习来解决

对于强化学习，首先需要定义```奖赏```,如果<a href="https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php?latex=\inline&space;$h&space;\le&space;0$" target="_blank"><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?\inline&space;$h&space;\le&space;0$" title="$h \le 0$" /></a>则给定大的惩罚，如果使用了向上的加速度，就给定小的惩罚。

```python
def flappy_reward(states, actions):
    """Rewards for flappy bird game."""
    reward = 0.0
    for (state, action) in zip(states, actions):
        _, height = state
        if height < 0:
            reward += 10 * height
        reward -= action
    return reward
```

该环境的策略

```python
def flappy_policy(theta, states, actions):
    """Linear map of last two states, ignoring previous actions."""
    if len(states) == 1:
        states = states + states
    return np.dot(theta, np.reshape(np.array(states[-2:]), (4,)))
def flappy_simulator(theta, num_steps):
    """Compute rewards of policy for given number of steps."""
    policy = lambda sts, ats: flappy_policy(theta, sts, ats)
    states, actions = unroll(flappy_bird, flappy_inits, policy, 
                             num_steps)
    return flappy_reward(states, actions)
```

那么，目标函数为

```python
def objective(theta, horizon=20):
    """Flappy bird search objective."""
    return -1.0*flappy_simulator(theta, horizon)
```

我们考虑使用随机优化算法来求解

```python
xs = random_search(objective, np.zeros(4), 10, gss)
policy = lambda states, actions: flappy_policy(xs[-1], states, actions)
states, actions = unroll(flappy_bird, flappy_inits, policy, 20)
heights = [h for (v, h) in states]

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
im = plt.imread('flappy.png')
fig.gca().imshow(im, aspect='auto', extent=(0, 1, 9.5, 10.5))
fig.figimage(im, 0, fig.bbox.ymax)
plt.plot(range(len(heights)), heights, **kwargs);
```
